00:16:57.560 --> 00:17:01.410
And then we have live classes as well
in the RAIO Family Facebook group,

238
00:17:01.480 --> 00:17:06.320
with me and my teachers to
teach you live and help you respond

239
00:17:06.320 --> 00:17:08.450
to all your questions and so forth.

240
00:17:08.520 --> 00:17:11.850
So the program works this way:

241
00:17:11.920 --> 00:17:17.250
In chapter one to four, we're going
to use the Interactive Stories method.

242
00:17:17.320 --> 00:17:20.170
This is a method that's going
to take you from your current level,

243
00:17:20.240 --> 00:17:23.600
it doesn't matter if you're starting
from zero or if you already

244
00:17:23.600 --> 00:17:24.850
speak a little bit of English.

245
00:17:24.920 --> 00:17:29.690
This method is going to take you from
that level to an advanced English level.

246
00:17:29.760 --> 00:17:33.320
And then in chapter 5
and 6, we're going to take you

247
00:17:33.390 --> 00:17:36.130
from advanced to fully fluent.

248
00:17:36.200 --> 00:17:41.210
In chapter 1 to 4, we're going
to use the Interactive Stories method.

249
00:17:41.280 --> 00:17:43.570
How this works is very simple.

250
00:17:43.640 --> 00:17:48.690
You're going to listen and you're going
to read stories and conversations.

251
00:17:48.760 --> 00:17:52.210
You're going to consume a lot
of English every single day,

252
00:17:52.280 --> 00:17:55.530
and that's going to help you
learn the language in a natural way.

253
00:17:55.600 --> 00:17:58.210
How it works is super simple.

254
00:17:58.280 --> 00:18:03.130
First, in every class,
there's an explanatory video.

255
00:18:03.200 --> 00:18:08.120
There's a video explaining
the class, the story, the conversation

256
00:18:08.180 --> 00:18:09.730
that you're going to listen to.

257
00:18:09.800 --> 00:18:11.410
You just click play here.

258
00:18:11.480 --> 00:18:14.170
You make sure you have
subtitles in your language.

259
00:18:14.240 --> 00:18:18.000
I recommend to have always
subtitles in Spanish so that

260
00:18:18.070 --> 00:18:20.930
you understand everything perfectly.

261
00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:23.960
Once you get a little better,
you can put subtitles in English

262
00:18:24.030 --> 00:18:25.730
or remove them altogether.

263
00:18:25.800 --> 00:18:27.600
You decide that.

264
00:18:28.120 --> 00:18:30.850
But the first thing you're going
to do in every single class

265
00:18:30.920 --> 00:18:32.320
is just to watch this video.

266
00:18:32.390 --> 00:18:36.330
You just click play,
and then you watch this video.

267
00:18:36.400 --> 00:18:41.890
Once you have watched this video,
you go to step number one.

268
00:18:41.960 --> 00:18:48.040
Step number one is to start listening
to the story a few times with

269
00:18:48.110 --> 00:18:49.930
a translation in Spanish.

270
00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:56.290
If we scroll down here, we're going
to have the story written out

271
00:18:56.360 --> 00:18:59.930
with subtitles and
a translation in Spanish.

272
00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:02.250
What's your goal here?

273
00:19:02.320 --> 00:19:06.370
It's to listen a few times until
you actually understand the story well.

274
00:19:06.440 --> 00:19:09.890
A few times, two,
three times should be enough

275
00:19:09.960 --> 00:19:11.930
until you understand the story well.

276
00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:16.650
Once you understand the story well,
you're going to go to step number two.

277
00:19:16.720 --> 00:19:20.560
In step number two, you have the same
story, the same conversation

278
00:19:20.630 --> 00:19:25.130
you're going to listen to,
but without the translation in Spanish.

279
00:19:25.200 --> 00:19:30.511
This time, I want you to listen many,
many times, over and over again,

280
00:19:30.711 --> 00:19:34.655
until you understand the story
with your eyes closed.

281
00:19:34.855 --> 00:19:37.250
Completely with your eyes closed.

282
00:19:37.320 --> 00:19:40.090
And that's going to require
many repetitions.

283
00:19:40.160 --> 00:19:45.930
You're probably going to have to listen 10
times, maybe 15 times, maybe 20 times,

284
00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:50.480
until you're able to understand
the story completely without looking

285
00:19:50.550 --> 00:19:52.610
at the text, with your eyes closed.

286
00:19:52.680 --> 00:19:56.290
And remember, that is how
language learning works.

287
00:19:56.360 --> 00:19:59.720
With a lot of repetition,
listening to the same vocabulary,

288
00:19:59.790 --> 00:20:02.320
to the same grammar over and over again.

289
00:20:02.390 --> 00:20:05.730
You're basically burning the language
into your long-term memory.

290
00:20:05.800 --> 00:20:08.840
That's how you learned Spanish
as a child, and that's how you're going

291
00:20:08.910 --> 00:20:10.570
to learn English as well.

292
00:20:10.640 --> 00:20:12.970
Remember, this is a new way of learning.

293
00:20:13.040 --> 00:20:17.090
So be patient and take your time
to adapt yourself to the method.

294
00:20:17.160 --> 00:20:18.890
There's no rush.

295
00:20:18.960 --> 00:20:23.040
Step number three, once you're able
to understand the story with your eyes

296
00:20:23.110 --> 00:20:27.490
closed, you're going to go to
the interactive version of the story.

297
00:20:27.560 --> 00:20:31.920
This is where you're going
to be practicing speaking,

298
00:20:31.990 --> 00:20:34.370
or responding to questions.

299
00:20:34.440 --> 00:20:38.560
What you're going to notice is this is
the same story or the same conversation

300
00:20:38.630 --> 00:20:41.410
