to in step one and two.

301
00:20:41.480 --> 00:20:46.320
But this time, there's going to be a
question after each sentence, and you're

302
00:20:46.390 --> 00:20:51.970
going to respond out loud, yes or no,
to this question as you're listening.

303
00:20:52.040 --> 00:20:53.680
You're going to do this
over and over again.

304
00:20:53.750 --> 00:20:55.410
You're going to practice this.

305
00:20:55.480 --> 00:20:57.450
The rule here is very simple:

306
00:20:57.520 --> 00:21:01.690
you're going to listen several times
until you are able to

307
00:21:01.760 --> 00:21:06.770
respond correctly to all the questions
on time with your eyes closed.

308
00:21:06.840 --> 00:21:07.850
And no worries.

309
00:21:07.920 --> 00:21:12.320
You're going to hear the correct response
being repeated as you're listening,

310
00:21:12.320 --> 00:21:13.680
so you know if you're right or not.

311
00:21:13.750 --> 00:21:18.170
It's a little bit of a testing
of your level in every single section.

312
00:21:18.240 --> 00:21:23.382
And you're going to have to do this
at least 10 times as well, most likely,

313
00:21:23.582 --> 00:21:26.283
until you're able to respond
correctly to all questions,

314
00:21:26.483 --> 00:21:27.730
on time with your eyes closed.

315
00:21:27.800 --> 00:21:32.890
When you're able to do that, that
means that you have completed this class.

316
00:21:32.960 --> 00:21:36.770
You can click here to go
to the next section.

317
00:21:36.840 --> 00:21:40.160
You can only go to the next section
when you are able to respond

318
00:21:40.230 --> 00:21:46.490
to all the questions correctly, out loud,
on time, without looking at the text.

319
00:21:46.560 --> 00:21:51.400
This is how you're going
to learn English, in chapter one to four.

320
00:21:51.400 --> 00:21:53.130
This is how we're going
to build up your level.

321
00:21:53.200 --> 00:21:56.170
What you're going to see
