to feel that it's a challenge anyways.

832
00:49:27.360 --> 00:49:32.120
Number eight, respond in your own language
for as long as you need.

833
00:49:32.400 --> 00:49:40.000
If you're in a conversation and everyone
speaks English and you don't speak

834
00:49:40.070 --> 00:49:43.290
well English yet, respond in Spanish.

835
00:49:43.360 --> 00:49:45.640
Keep that fluency going.

836
00:49:45.710 --> 00:49:50.810
Remember, the most important thing is you
listening to English, not speaking.

837
00:49:50.880 --> 00:49:52.090
Speaking will come.

838
00:49:52.160 --> 00:49:55.730
So feel free to respond in your
own language for as long as you need.

839
00:49:55.800 --> 00:49:59.529
I know this is different from school where
the teacher forces you,

840
00:49:59.729 --> 00:50:02.490
"Speak English, repeat after me,
speak, speak, speak!"

841
00:50:02.560 --> 00:50:06.690
No, you never have to force speaking ever.

842
00:50:06.760 --> 00:50:08.090
That's a mistake.

843
00:50:08.160 --> 00:50:10.730
Those teachers are not
language learning experts.

844
00:50:10.800 --> 00:50:11.490
Take it easy.

845
00:50:11.560 --> 00:50:15.160
You don't need to respond in English
unless you feel comfortable

846
00:50:15.160 --> 00:50:16.001
responding in English.

847
00:50:16.201 --> 00:50:16.690
It doesn't matter.

848
00:50:16.760 --> 00:50:18.930
The most important thing is listening.

849
00:50:19.000 --> 00:50:20.320
That's the same with number nine.

850
00:50:20.390 --> 00:50:22.730
Don't ask people to correct you.

851
00:50:22.800 --> 00:50:29.930
I know it's easy to think that
we need people to correct us, to improve.

852
00:50:30.000 --> 00:50:38.480
And that's not correct, because when
we get constantly corrected, we actually

853
00:50:38.550 --> 00:50:41.530
