863
00:51:13.840 --> 00:51:17.650
You corrected yourself when
you kept listening to good Spanish.

864
00:51:17.720 --> 00:51:20.490
That's how you finally corrected yourself.

865
00:51:20.560 --> 00:51:25.330
It wasn't because someone taught you
or told you about your mistakes.

866
00:51:25.400 --> 00:51:28.810
So don't waste your time
asking people to correct you.

867
00:51:28.880 --> 00:51:31.770
It's only going to affect your confidence.

868
00:51:31.840 --> 00:51:33.080
Ten, be patient.

869
00:51:33.150 --> 00:51:34.810
Languages don't have an end.

870
00:51:34.880 --> 00:51:36.250
Find joy in the process.

871
00:51:36.320 --> 00:51:37.880
Consistency over intensity.

872
00:51:37.950 --> 00:51:40.010
Be consistent every single day.

873
00:51:40.080 --> 00:51:41.890
If you need help, ask.

874
00:51:41.960 --> 00:51:44.650
The worst thing you can do is stop.

875
00:51:44.720 --> 00:51:48.610
Thirteen, your speaking will always
be worse than your understanding.

876
00:51:48.680 --> 00:51:51.130
You're going to be better
at reading than listening.

877
00:51:51.200 --> 00:51:53.690
You're going to be better
at listening than speaking.

878
00:51:53.760 --> 00:51:56.210
That's just the way
language learning works.

879
00:51:56.280 --> 00:51:59.890
Your speaking and your listening ability
will come over time

880
00:51:59.960 --> 00:52:02.890
